post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Constitutions can be amended by the Federal Government to suit their policies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This claim is speculative. The correlation between drugs and \\(violent\\) crime is observable. The causes for that correlation are not necessarily observable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many [deaths](http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-24581947) attributed to ecstasy \\(or MDMA\\) use are actually caused by other, unwanted ingredients.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalizing drugs will not automatically remove the prejudice. If people see those on drugs being violent or a nuisance to society, the prejudice will likely remain. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Aquiring drugs in a legal setting allows for regulation that may require informing the buyer about dangerous combinations, or avoid selling to people already under the influence of other drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If a government wanted to put money into harm reduction, it could do so without legalising drugs in order to avoid the costs of enforcing a drug prohibition. It could instead cut other government programs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap [substitutes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desomorphine#Toxicity_of_%22krokodil%22) like krokodil cause severe health problems. If drugs were legal and cheaper, substitutes lose popularity.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If someone is willing to commit an act as vile as date raping someone, they're probably not going to care very much about whether they have to purchase the drug illegally."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The cost of alcohol was roughly 3 times higher during prohibition than compared to previous prices \\([pg. 7](http://www.nber.org/papers/w3675.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Opiates have a [rich history](https://www.history.com/topics/crime/history-of-heroin-morphine-and-opiates) of recreational use, with the Ancient Sumerians calling it "The Joy Plant".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Benzodiazepines are [readily available](http://w-bad.org/statistics/) in most countries for common complaints like insomnia, jet lag and performance anxiety, and are actually more effective at increasing the effects of alcohol than barbiturates.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This does not take into account plants that do not grow well everywhere. For these cases, there is still a reliance on other communities that fall under different legislation to cultivate the plants. This keeps a connection with the international criminal drug trade.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use has a negative effect on freedom and, therefore, ought to be contained.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since adults would prefer the legal market, these people would have to base their entire business on selling to underaged people. This would make it drastically less profitable, as well as easier to expose by police.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A significant number of individuals are already drawn to legal addictive substances, for instance, cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Date-rape drugs are controlled presently. The current prohibition has not hindered the occurrence of date rape.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Children of drug addicts would have a much higher chance of receiving the appropriate help if drug users did not have to hide.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Albert Hofman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Hofmann), the creator of LSD, took LSD for over two decades without any health implications.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various governments have already facilitated access to drugs and positive outcomes have come of this.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although education and information on the harmful side effects of [smoking](https://edition.cnn.com/2014/01/11/health/still-smoking/index.html) have been around for decades, millions of people still smoke.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Such stress might be irrational, especially when it's related to unproblematic drug use. In that case, the psychological stress is the fault of the persons irrational beliefs."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs could lead to better education on how to be safe around them. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugging and raping someone is way more risky than buying illegal drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'When the government legalizes something, it \\(unintentionally\\) sends the message that the substance is acceptable and a legitimate form of recreation. This may encourage people to become involved in drug taking.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The argument that illicit drugs can lead to addiction and should therefore be banned is a double standard, as various legal activities and substances are equally or even more addictive. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That correlation is not affected by their legality. So, legalization will not make it worse unless it causes the price to go down. Given the emphasis many put on drug taxes as an argument in favor of legalization, that seems unlikely.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs have recreational and social value.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The cost of alcohol was roughly 3 times higher during prohibition than compared to previous prices \\([pg. 7](http://www.nber.org/papers/w3675.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mushrooms and MDMA](http://www.ias.org.uk/uploads/pdf/News%20stories/dnutt-lancet-011110.pdf) have been classed safer than tobacco and alcohol. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The war on drugs has [cost civilian lives](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prosecution takes place after the repercussions have occurred. A ban can prevent them from ever happening.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates with criminality, thievery, and risky sexual behavior. Responsibility is a state that is easily bypassed when you enter the flow of the drug world.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tobacco farming before abolition was [done by slaves](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_in_the_American_colonies). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Safety of irresponsible people shouldn't come at the expense of freedom of responsible people."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has released inaccurate or untruthful information about drugs in an attempt to stop the public from using them. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine is [highly addictive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_dependence) and easy to become dependent on. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If someone is willing to commit an act as vile as date raping someone, they're probably not going to care very much about whether they have to purchase the drug illegally."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs could make people live and learn life as it is. Bad decisions are a part of life.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Having any positive impacts at all is not to be conflated with being a net positive, or fully positive.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mushrooms and MDMA](http://www.ias.org.uk/uploads/pdf/News%20stories/dnutt-lancet-011110.pdf) have been classed safer than tobacco and alcohol. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Current drug legislation undermines governmental legitimacy as well as \\(moral\\) authority of the law, as governmental action is not based on facts, evidence and latest research but on outdated knowledge as well as on ideology.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Alcohol](https://theconversation.com/alcohol-leads-to-more-violence-than-other-drugs-but-youd-never-know-from-the-headlines-72281) is responsible for more violence and harm than any other drug.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The number of deaths from overdose will rise dramatically as a result of easy access to drugs including meth, MDMA, and heroin. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will be seen as a sign of the government/authority giving up on protecting people from the harm they could do, to themselves and others, through poorly selected drug use.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Shooting galleries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_injection_site) could be provided by the government as a safe environment for those requiring them. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Suicide rates may increase as overdose will be an easily accessible option.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prosecution takes place after the repercussions have occurred. A ban can prevent them from ever happening.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If legalized, the users wouldn't have the same incentive to rid themselves of the evidence as quickly as possible."}
